<dd>First off, because I simply do not want to. I simply do not want to be involved with anything that might be a hassle, as this is just a hobby for me. As soon as it&#39;s no longer is fun for me, I&#39;ll lose all interest. Second, any opinions I write on main space are accountable to reliable sources. I try to avoid those altogether, though, doing most of my edits on technical articles. I have no doubt that there are all types of people on Wikipedia, and the fact that we, ideally, are all equals here is one of the best things about this place. But, really, the best way to judge the quality of any editor is not by the name, but by the quality of their contributions.</dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>


