<ul>
<li>Strongly agree that discouraging <a href="" title="WP:OWN">WP:OWN</a> would be of benefit. Some editors do not allow editing of &#34;their&#34; articles, and some  monitor the article talk page and unilaterally decide what &#34;consensus&#34; is. When a new or casual editor encounters this behaviour, I can see why they do not want to contribute further to the encyclopaedia. &#38;mdash;<a href="" title="User:Mattisse">&#60;font color=&#34;navy&#34;&#62;<b>Mattisse</b>&#60;/font&#62;</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:Mattisse">Talk</a>) 19:15, 24 July 2009 (UTC)</li></ul>
